network_overview: The capture contains two independent, successful IMS-SIP registration dialogs (VoLTE/VoNR) between the UE (10.235.69.1) and two different P-CSCFs (10.235.68.68 & 10.235.68.65) carried over SCTP on the Mw interface; no calls or media are present and no errors were detected.

observations.finding: Two short SIP registration transactions (4 & 2 pkts) completed in <130 ms each, indicating normal control-plane load.
No RTP/RTCP observed; media plane not yet established, so voice-quality metrics are not applicable.

recommendations.action: Enable periodic OPTIONS ping from P-CSCF toward registered UE to detect silent failures early.
recommendations.rationale: Adds lightweight keep-alive without re-registration load; improves failover detection.

recommendations.action: Collect matching GTP-C/GTP-U capture for the same UE to verify dedicated VoLTE bearer setup latency.
recommendations.rationale: Ensures user-plane resources are allocated within 3GPP 500 ms target after 200 OK.

recommendations.action: Confirm SIP-over-SCTP multi-homing on P-CSCF to eliminate single-homed SCTP association risk.
recommendations.rationale: Prevents call-drop during transport path failure; aligns with TS 23.228 redundancy.

session_analysis.signaling_health: 100 % success: both REGISTER transactions received 200 OK within 120 ms, no retransmissions or 3xx/4xx/5xx responses.
session_analysis.user_plane_health: No GTP tunnels observed; user-plane not yet established (registration-only trace).
session_analysis.voice_quality: No RTP flows; QoS metrics (MOS, packet-loss, jitter) not measurable in this control-plane snapshot.
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: Signaling plane is healthy; bearer creation (GTP-C/U) expected immediately after 200 OK but absent in current capture.
